{
  "texts": [
    "To manage communication conflicts and maintain coherence, IoA systems require sequential speaking mechanisms that regulate speaking turns during group collaboration [7], [45].• Polling Mechanism: A coordinator sequentially queries agents for their states or opinions, enforcing only one agent speaks at a time to reduce collisions.",
    "For instance, in [7], Chen et al.",
    "model the conversation flow as a finite state machine with five predefined state, where LLMs autonomously manage state transitions to coordinate collaboration.",
    "Although effective for maintaining order, it introduces latency and may become a bottleneck in largescale deployments.",
    "• Arbitration Control: When conflicts arise, a third-party arbitrator (e.g., higher-tie agent or rule engine) can resolve contentions and assigns speaking rights or priorities, ensuring conflict resolution across agents."
  ]
}